{"lemma":"بارِد","slug":"بارِد","root":"ب.ر.د","root_slug":"ب-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بارِد","root":"برد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2234"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cold, cooling"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dull, slow"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"poor (wit, poetry)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"incontestable (right)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"safely placed (money)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of بَرَدَ (barada, “to be cold, to freeze”). Cognate with Amharic ብርድ (bɨrd)."},"ipa":["/baː.rid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2234","headword_ar":"بَارِدٌ","root":"brd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cold; chill; cool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;) applied to water [&c.]; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodN","text_ar":"بَرْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally an inf. n., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", used as an epithet,] (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baruwdN","text_ar":"بَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buraAdN","text_ar":"بُرَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) but the last two are intensive forms [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very cold"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chill"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cool"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loved, beloved, liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayo$N baArdN","text_ar":"عَيْشٌ بَاردٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An easy and a pleasant life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, * T, * M, A, L, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN baAridapN AlEayo$i","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ بَارِدَةٌ العَيْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayo$i","text_ar":"العَيْشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barodapu","text_ar":"بَرْدَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the latter written in the TT"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baradapu AlEy$","text_ar":"بَرَدَةُ العيش"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A night of easy and pleasant life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganymapN baAridapN","text_ar":"غَنيمَةٌ بَارِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter word. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samuwmN baAridN","text_ar":"سَمُومٌ بَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hot wind that is constant, continual, permanent, settled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incessant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY Ealayohi A^alofN baAridN","text_ar":"لِى عَلَيْهِ اَلْفٌ بَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thousand"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pieces of money &c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory, on him, to me, and established against him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are owed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"due, to me, by,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M. *) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN baAridFA mux~uhu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ بَارِدًا مُخُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baArida AlEiZaAma","text_ar":"بَارِدَ العِظَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came in a lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an emaciated, state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the contr. case, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~aA mux~uhu","text_ar":"حَارَّا مُخُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAr~a AlEiZaAmi","text_ar":"حَارَّ العِظَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b6-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAridN","text_ar":"بَارِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blunt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a sword and the like: see 1. ―         -b7-  And, contr., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for you say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murohafaAtN bawaAridu","text_ar":"مُرْهَفَاتٌ بَوَارِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAridapN","text_ar":"بَارِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cutting, swords:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaying swords."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}